  <prompt>
    With `ExecuteAnalysisAsync` deleted (task 042), the `sprk_actiontypeid` lookup field on `sprk_analysisaction`
    has no runtime reader. Per FR-03, drop the field from Dataverse. Use the `dataverse-create-schema` skill
    pattern (Web API + PowerShell) — PAC CLI does NOT have direct `pac column delete`. Before deletion,
    verify schema state via MCP `mcp__dataverse__describe_table("sprk_analysisaction")`. After deletion,
    re-describe to confirm field is gone. Task 044 (drop `sprk_executoractiontype` INT) follows sequentially.
    Tasks 043 and 044 form a sequential schema-cascade pair.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Dataverse platform engineer dropping a schema field via Web API. Goal: clean removal,
    no orphan references, MCP-verified pre/post state. Mirror the `dataverse-create-schema` skill's
    deletion pattern (inverse of attribute creation).
  </role>

  <goal>
    1. Pre-deletion MCP verification: `sprk_actiontypeid` exists on `sprk_analysisaction` and has zero load-bearing readers post-task 042
    2. PowerShell script written to delete the attribute (idempotent; safe-rerun)
    3. Field removed from Dataverse `sprk_analysisaction` entity in spaarkedev1
    4. Post-deletion MCP verification: field absent from entity
    5. Any orphan code references in `src/server/` discovered + flagged for task 046 (`AnalysisActionService` cleanup follows)
    6. Solution exported + committed (per dataverse-deploy convention) — optional based on solution shape
