    </step>
    <step order="2" name="MCP pre-check — verify field exists">
      Call: mcp__dataverse__describe(table="sprk_analysisaction")
      Confirm `sprk_actiontypeid` is present in the entity's attribute list. Note its LogicalName, AttributeType (Lookup), and Targets (should be sprk_analysisactiontype).
      If absent — STOP and report (field may already be dropped; task is a no-op).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Code-side pre-check — confirm no runtime reader">
      Run: Grep pattern="sprk_actiontypeid" glob="**/*.cs" output_mode="content" -n true
      Expected post-task-042: zero hits in production code (any hits in `tests/` flagged for task 046).
      If production code still references the field — STOP and report (task 041 or 042 missed something).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Verify the lookup TABLE is preserved (FR-05)">
      Call: mcp__dataverse__describe(table="sprk_analysisactiontype")
      Confirm the table itself exists and is intact. The table stays per FR-05. We're deleting the FK column on `sprk_analysisaction`, not the table.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author deletion PowerShell script">
      Create: `scripts/dataverse/Drop-Sprk-Analysisaction-Actiontypeid.ps1`
      Pattern (inverse of attribute creation per dataverse-create-schema skill):
      - Acquire Dataverse Web API token (Azure CLI auth)
      - Test-AttributeExists for `sprk_actiontypeid` on `sprk_analysisaction`
      - If exists: DELETE EntityDefinitions(LogicalName='sprk_analysisaction')/Attributes(LogicalName='sprk_actiontypeid')
      - Wait + PublishXml for the entity to refresh metadata
      - Re-test absence; emit success message
      - Make idempotent (re-run shows "already deleted")
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Run script in dry-run mode (if implemented) OR review the DELETE call carefully">
      Visual review the DELETE call shape. Confirm correct entity + attribute LogicalName. This is destructive — no undo without restore-from-backup.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Run script against spaarkedev1">
      Execute the deletion script. Capture stdout for the task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="MCP post-check — verify field absent">
      Call: mcp__dataverse__describe(table="sprk_analysisaction")
      Required: `sprk_actiontypeid` NOT in the attribute list. This is the FR-03 acceptance signal.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify lookup TABLE still present (FR-05 guard)">
      Call: mcp__dataverse__describe(table="sprk_analysisactiontype")
      Required: table still exists (FR-05). Document this in task notes.
